# LangGraph patterns (protocol)

## When to use

**Use** for multi-step flows: conditional logic, read/write separation, state accumulation, parallel map-reduce.

**Do not use** for simple CRUD, a single LLM call, or a straight line of agent calls.

## File layout

- One graph per `{domain}.graph.ts`: factory, nodes, and inline state (`Annotation.Root` + reducers).

## Factory

Factory class takes **dependencies** (database, embedder, agents, …) via **constructor**. No hardcoded infra imports inside the graph module.

## Nodes

- Async functions: `(state) => partialState`.
- **Catch errors inside nodes** — do not throw uncaught.
- Name: `{action}Node` (e.g. `evaluateNode`).

## Routing

Every graph needs **at least one conditional edge**. Every branch must map to a **valid node name** or **END**.

## Checklist

- [ ] Conditional edge(s)
- [ ] `Annotation.Root` state with reducers
- [ ] Factory with DI (no hidden globals)
- [ ] Node error handling (no throw-through)
- [ ] Fast paths where possible
- [ ] Routing tests
